        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-04-17 12:18:00.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 17:\n\nHi,\n\nCould you please review these changes? They refer to SDC-2499, which fixes many of the problems related to the testing of asdctool. It is part of a topic which goal is to separate the report writing and formatting logic to improve maintainability and testability.\n\nIn this change, we finally decouple the report's writing and formatting logic. The goal is to improve testability by making the report writing configurable. This prevents passing nulls to multiple functions in tests when writing is not a concern using a console writer. Ultimately, we could even prevent any file writing in the tests, and create an in-memory writer (this still has to be done). Also there is still some refactoring to be done related to the ArtifactToolBl class but this will be addressed later.\n\nThank you in advance for your help.\n\nFrancis.",
        "patchset_number": 17
      },
